{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-88dcb123e69566c1", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# AISHELL-5: The First Open-Source In-Car Multi-Channel Multi-Speaker Speech Dataset for Automatic Speech Diarization and Recognition\narXiv: 2505.23036\nAuthors: Yuhang Dai, He Wang, Xingchen Li, Zihan Zhang, Shuiyuan Wang, Lei Xie, Xin Xu, Hongxiao Guo, Shaoji Zhang, Hui Bu, Wei Chen\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of AISHELL-5, the first open-source multi-channel, multi-speaker in-car Mandarin speech dataset for automatic speech diarization and recognition.\n  2. Provision of over 100 hours of real multi-channel speech data recorded across more than 60 diverse driving scenarios.\n  3. Inclusion of 40 hours of real-world environmental noise recordings to support in-car speech data simulation.\n  4. Release of an open-access, reproducible baseline system integrating speech source separation and automatic speech recognition modules.\n  5. Demonstration of the challenges of in-car speech processing by evaluating various mainstream ASR models on the dataset.\n\nTags: ASR/训练-监督, Eval/基准", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6847692e-4f91-4cd0-afdc-9fa357533845", "uuid": "da896a48-7c5d-46fb-a41d-5dd29f1db9dc", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T13:47:54.453Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# AISHELL-5: The First Open-Source In-Car Multi-Channel Multi-Speaker Speech Dataset for Automatic Speech Diarization and Recognition\narXiv: 2505.23036\nAuthors: Yuhang Dai, He Wang, Xingchen Li, Zihan Zhang, Shuiyuan Wang, Lei Xie, Xin Xu, Hongxiao Guo, Shaoji Zhang, Hui Bu, Wei Chen\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of AISHELL-5, the first open-source multi-channel, multi-speaker in-car Mandarin speech dataset for automatic speech diarization and recognition.\n  2. Provision of over 100 hours of real multi-channel speech data recorded across more than 60 diverse driving scenarios.\n  3. Inclusion of 40 hours of real-world environmental noise recordings to support in-car speech data simulation.\n  4. Release of an open-access, reproducible baseline system integrating speech source separation and automatic speech recognition modules.\n  5. Demonstration of the challenges of in-car speech processing by evaluating various mainstream ASR models on the dataset.\n\nTags: ASR/训练-监督, Eval/基准", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b81611a838f5bb32", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# GigaSpeech 2: An Evolving, Large-Scale and Multi-domain ASR Corpus for Low-Resource Languages with Automated Crawling, Transcription and Refinement\narXiv: 2406.11546\nAuthors: Yifan Yang, Zheshu Song, Jianheng Zhuo, Mingyu Cui, Jinpeng Li, Bo Yang, Yexing Du, Ziyang Ma, Xunying Liu, Ziyuan Wang, Ke Li, Shuai Fan, Kai Yu, Wei-Qiang Zhang, Guoguo Chen, Xie Chen\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We release GigaSpeech 2, a large-scale, multi-domain, multilingual ASR corpus containing raw and refined versions of automatically transcribed Thai, Indonesian, and Vietnamese speech.\n  2. We develop an automated pipeline for data crawling, transcription, and label refinement that constructs large-scale speech datasets without relying on labeled data.\n  3. We propose a modified Noisy Student Training method that iteratively refines flawed pseudo labels through scaling, relabeling, and filtering to significantly improve data quality.\n  4. We release challenging and realistic speech recognition test sets for Thai, Indonesian, and Vietnamese that better reflect real-world ASR scenarios than previous public test sets.\n  5. We demonstrate that ASR models trained on GigaSpeech 2 outperform competitive baselines, including Whisper large-v3 and commercial services, across multiple evaluation sets.\n\nTags: ASR", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6847692e-4f91-4cd0-afdc-9fa357533845", "uuid": "bc3fbe6f-f3be-4429-8665-24c2334f0468", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T13:47:54.694Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# GigaSpeech 2: An Evolving, Large-Scale and Multi-domain ASR Corpus for Low-Resource Languages with Automated Crawling, Transcription and Refinement\narXiv: 2406.11546\nAuthors: Yifan Yang, Zheshu Song, Jianheng Zhuo, Mingyu Cui, Jinpeng Li, Bo Yang, Yexing Du, Ziyang Ma, Xunying Liu, Ziyuan Wang, Ke Li, Shuai Fan, Kai Yu, Wei-Qiang Zhang, Guoguo Chen, Xie Chen\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We release GigaSpeech 2, a large-scale, multi-domain, multilingual ASR corpus containing raw and refined versions of automatically transcribed Thai, Indonesian, and Vietnamese speech.\n  2. We develop an automated pipeline for data crawling, transcription, and label refinement that constructs large-scale speech datasets without relying on labeled data.\n  3. We propose a modified Noisy Student Training method that iteratively refines flawed pseudo labels through scaling, relabeling, and filtering to significantly improve data quality.\n  4. We release challenging and realistic speech recognition test sets for Thai, Indonesian, and Vietnamese that better reflect real-world ASR scenarios than previous public test sets.\n  5. We demonstrate that ASR models trained on GigaSpeech 2 outperform competitive baselines, including Whisper large-v3 and commercial services, across multiple evaluation sets.\n\nTags: ASR", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
